data.name: _ltfOptionsNoteLabel.Text
data.value:
LTD is LEAD Temporary Document Format. when saving to LTD, the recognition result of the pages are appended to an LTD file on disk. You can save the result of multiple OCR operation on a single LTD file in case the OCR engine is not be able to hold all the pages in memory.
You cannot view the result document directly. Instead, you must use the LTDMergeDemo or the File/Convert LTD menu item inside the OcrDemo or OcrMultiEngineDemo to convert the LTD file to the final requested format.

data.name: _emfOptionsNoteLabel.Text
data.value: Note that the EMF format does not support multiple-pages, hence when saving a multi-page document to EMF the result is the last page only.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: This format uses text flow and using frames helps achieve maximum resembling between the input file and final generated document since the document writer can place objects using absolute (X and Y) position parameters.
